    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1687813937" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1687813937" />
    <a title="Gabriel Baquero" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57350353-gabriel-baquero"><img alt="Gabriel Baquero" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1619986384p2/57350353.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1687813937?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabriel Baquero" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabriel Baquero" href="/user/show/57350353-gabriel-baquero">Gabriel Baquero</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25863396-la-anarqu-a">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57350353-gabriel-baquero?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57350353-gabriel-baquero?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57350353-gabriel-baquero?shelf=anarchism">anarchism</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1687813937" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15589306071957476668">So I finally finished reading Errico Malatesta&apos;s pamphlet &quot;Anarchy&quot;. I think it&apos;s a pretty good introduction to classical anarchist thought, which could of course be complemented with some contemporary perspectives. I noticed a dash of positivism in Malatesta&apos;s discourse, much like in Marx&apos;s, and a whole lot of influence from Kropotkin&apos;s biological outlook. His anthropological idea of how domination came to be would be very well reinforced by what we now know about the role of agriculture in the</span>
  <span id="freeText15589306071957476668" style="display:none">So I finally finished reading Errico Malatesta's pamphlet "Anarchy". I think it's a pretty good introduction to classical anarchist thought, which could of course be complemented with some contemporary perspectives. I noticed a dash of positivism in Malatesta's discourse, much like in Marx's, and a whole lot of influence from Kropotkin's biological outlook. His anthropological idea of how domination came to be would be very well reinforced by what we now know about the role of agriculture in the first production of a surplus and thus the origin of private property and State and class domination. Also, I could detect all the flaws that the Krisis Group and Moishe Postone argue are to be found in the Left's traditional thinking, such as a lack of understanding of the very important role that commodity fetishism and value play in capitalism, as well as other very important fetishistic categories such as labor. Most anarchists and Marxists, Malatesta included, believe that work and labor are transhistorical categories which exist independently before and after capitalism, rather than viewing them as what they really are: fetishistic categories immanent to capitalism itself. Thus, classical anarchists like Malatesta call for the abolition of private property (while historical experiences like the USSR demonstrate that capitalism can exist without private property and a market economy), but not the abolition of work and labor themselves, like the Krisis Group thinkers and some post-Left anarchists such as Bob Black do. All in all, Malatesta's "Anarchy" functions as a good primer on classical anarchist ideals, but its shortcomings are pretty evident in light of all the things that have happened since it was written.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15589306071957476668" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

