<div id="review_3764598164" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3764598164" />
    <a title="José" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50673646-jos"><img alt="José" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451239528p2/50673646.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3764598164?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="José" class="user" itemprop="url" name="José" href="/user/show/50673646-jos">José</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50673646-jos?shelf=manifesto">manifesto</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50673646-jos?shelf=essays">essays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50673646-jos?shelf=economy">economy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3764598164" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14548769453975184199">This is an interesting manifesto-type of book. In it, Malatesta draws his theory of anarchism - anarcho-communism or as he calls it &quot;anarchism without adjectives&quot; - and how it can be built by recognising that humanity has progressed so much thanks to the solidarity it has adopted in order to overcome problems imposed by nature and that competition only exists to bid humans against humans. His other fundamental claim is that governments only exist as mediators of this competition and as those not</span>
  <span id="freeText14548769453975184199" style="display:none">This is an interesting manifesto-type of book. In it, Malatesta draws his theory of anarchism - anarcho-communism or as he calls it "anarchism without adjectives" - and how it can be built by recognising that humanity has progressed so much thanks to the solidarity it has adopted in order to overcome problems imposed by nature and that competition only exists to bid humans against humans. His other fundamental claim is that governments only exist as mediators of this competition and as those not only allowing, but also maintaining oppression, and that as soon as solidarity becomes the fundamental principle of society governments will no longer be useful or necessary. It is a completely different way of thinking about how society is structured written by the de facto leader of anarchy in Italy. It lacks the detailed and practical aspects of how this new society would work but that is not what one would expect from a manifesto - instead it focuses on explaining the fundamental principles that would rule the new humanity. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14548769453975184199" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

