<div id="review_3685221189" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3685221189" />
    <a title="Seburath" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64825162-seburath"><img alt="Seburath" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624915067p2/64825162.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3685221189?book_show_action=true">Dec 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Seburath" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Seburath" href="/user/show/64825162-seburath">Seburath</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3685221189" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12026443266483605649">In this short book of only 54 pages, Malatesta fails to explain what he is proposing...<br/><br/>Literally, he says: <br/><br/>&quot;If indeed our readers expect a reply from us to these questions, or at least to those which are really serious and important, which is more than our personal opinion at this particular moment, it means that we have failed in our attempt to explain to them what anarchism is about.&quot;<br/><br/>Translated:<br/><br/>&quot;If you are taking this seriously and have serious questions, it means you are dumb.&quot;<br/><br/>Malatesta criti</span>
  <span id="freeText12026443266483605649" style="display:none">In this short book of only 54 pages, Malatesta fails to explain what he is proposing...<br /><br />Literally, he says: <br /><br />"If indeed our readers expect a reply from us to these questions, or at least to those which are really serious and important, which is more than our personal opinion at this particular moment, it means that we have failed in our attempt to explain to them what anarchism is about."<br /><br />Translated:<br /><br />"If you are taking this seriously and have serious questions, it means you are dumb."<br /><br />Malatesta criticizes that people rely on a metaphysic concept of state so he wants to replace it with the metaphysic concept of solidarity, just like some libertarians rely on the metaphysic concept of market, without explaining or even giving insights!<br /><br />I must say that before going into these contradictions, this book was inspiring! But he raises too many expectations to finally explaining nothing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12026443266483605649" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


