<div id="review_3150046088" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3150046088" />
    <a title="Sami Eerola" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27578089-sami-eerola"><img alt="Sami Eerola" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577883534p2/27578089.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3150046088?book_show_action=true">Jun 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sami Eerola" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sami Eerola" href="/user/show/27578089-sami-eerola">Sami Eerola</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27578089-sami-eerola?shelf=read-in-2020">read-in-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3150046088" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13762710805043856078">Very simple and clear presentation of Anarchism theory and practice. The core is still interesting and well thought out, but some others are clearly outdated. For example Malatesta did not predict that a peoples militia guarding a revolution from a capitalist resurgent would entail surveillance, creating a new hierarchy. <br/><br/>Then Malatesta did not predict that in the future wars would be fought with bombs and not only soldiers. So a peoples militia being more courageous that an regular army is not a</span>
  <span id="freeText13762710805043856078" style="display:none">Very simple and clear presentation of Anarchism theory and practice. The core is still interesting and well thought out, but some others are clearly outdated. For example Malatesta did not predict that a peoples militia guarding a revolution from a capitalist resurgent would entail surveillance, creating a new hierarchy. <br /><br />Then Malatesta did not predict that in the future wars would be fought with bombs and not only soldiers. So a peoples militia being more courageous that an regular army is not as great defence, when the enemy has bombs. Anarchists got to know personally this in Spain and Soviet Union. <br /><br />But otherwise the theory of workers independent rule by collective mutual rule is still relevant. Especially the chapter about individual anarchist (today most are anarchocapitalists) and how their point of view is more authoritarian than the collectivists </span>
  <a data-text-id="13762710805043856078" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


