<div id="review_3691747670" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3691747670" />
    <a title="Logan Platt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/122309910-logan-platt"><img alt="Logan Platt" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3691747670?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Logan Platt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Logan Platt" href="/user/show/122309910-logan-platt">Logan Platt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3691747670" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7254166274861449327">Many of the ideas expressed I quite enjoyed. For example, sections regarding the over exaggerated significance of Darwinian competition to oppose co-operation. Co-operation is crucial in the preservation of our species and is, therefore, inherently self preserving. I also agree that the state is a tool for class suppression. Where I begin to disagree is Malatesta&apos;s brutal antagonism to socialist states. I understand the context and follow the arguments, but in revolutionary context, suppression </span>
  <span id="freeText7254166274861449327" style="display:none">Many of the ideas expressed I quite enjoyed. For example, sections regarding the over exaggerated significance of Darwinian competition to oppose co-operation. Co-operation is crucial in the preservation of our species and is, therefore, inherently self preserving. I also agree that the state is a tool for class suppression. Where I begin to disagree is Malatesta's brutal antagonism to socialist states. I understand the context and follow the arguments, but in revolutionary context, suppression of the capitalist class is necessary imo. I agree this is how society should be structured and anarchism is the goal, but it is natural to disagree on the means to achieve this. Overall, a great read and a perspective at which must be considered in radical organizing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7254166274861449327" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


